main event: A ground radar station in Quebec, Canada detected an unidentified flying object on August 8, 1961.
interesting points: The object was observed on radar for approximately 15 minutes., The sighting was reported by a Canadian source., The conclusions section of the report suggested it could be a balloon or aircraft., The report includes information from a telephone call about an explosion in the air in the vicinity., Similar explosions were reported in the area around the same date.
